{"updated_at": {"date": {"d": "30", "m": "06", "Y": "2026"}, "time": {"H": "07", "M": "40", "S": "15"}}, "news": [{"title": "Musi oustees to get 2BHK houses: Telangana housing minister", "para": "Telangana's Revenue Minister Ponguleti Srinivas Reddy has assured families displaced by the Musi rejuvenation project will receive 2 BHK homes and lawful compensation. The ambitious project aims to transform the Musi River into a tourism and economic hub for Hyderabad, ensuring flood control, water treatment, and enhanced green spaces.  The government emphasized a humane approach, prioritizing the welfare of the poor and preventing any injustice in the name of development.", "href": "https://realty.economictimes.indiatimes.com/news/residential/telangana-to-provide-2bhk-houses-to-musi-project-oustees/132083484?utm_source=newslisting&utm_medium=latestNews", "img": "data:image/png;base64, ", "img-src": "https://etimg.etb2bimg.com/thumb/img-size-921094/132083484.cms?width=150&height=112", "tag": "residential"}, {"title": "NGT ban triggers sand shortage, prices surge across Jharkhand", "para": "Sand prices have skyrocketed in Jharkhand, with truckloads costing up to Rs 55,000, due to the National Green Tribunal's mining ban until October 15. This has stalled construction projects and forced builders to source sand from Bihar, increasing costs significantly. Developers cite a lack of policy action and alleged black-marketing as contributing factors to the ongoing shortage and price hike, impacting lower economic groups.", "href": "https://realty.economictimes.indiatimes.com/news/allied-industries/ngt-ban-on-sand-mining-causes-prices-to-soar-in-jharkhand/132083462?utm_source=newslisting&utm_medium=latestNews", "img": "data:image/png;base64, ", "img-src": "https://etimg.etb2bimg.com/thumb/img-size-22470/132083462.cms?width=150&height=112", "tag": "allied-industries"}, {"title": "Land conversion norms set for major overhaul to boost business in Rajasthan", "para": "Rajasthan's revenue department is set to simplify land use changes, allowing conversions in planned and unplanned areas with a fee, eliminating separate approvals. This move aims to boost ease of doing business by reducing regulatory hurdles and delays that have long troubled industries. The reforms, part of the Centre's Business Reforms Action Plan, are expected to enhance transparency, speed up project approvals, and attract more private investment to the state.", "href": "https://realty.economictimes.indiatimes.com/news/industry/rajasthan-unveils-major-land-conversion-reforms-to-enhance-business-environment/132083274?utm_source=newslisting&utm_medium=latestNews", "img": "data:image/png;base64, ", "img-src": "https://etimg.etb2bimg.com/thumb/img-size-1838034/132083274.cms?width=150&height=112", "tag": "industry"}]}